  "local_port": 55536,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some things new employees should know going into their first day at Universal?",
  "response": "Starting a new job at Universal can be an exciting experience. Here are some essential things new employees should know before their first day:\n\n1. **Orientation and Onboarding**: Familiarize yourself with the schedule for your orientation or onboarding process. This may include introductions to company policies, benefits, and training sessions.\n\n2. **Dress Code**: Understand the dress code for your position. Universal often has specific attire requirements, especially for those working in guest-facing roles or attractions.\n\n3. **Arrival Time**: Plan to arrive early on your first day to account for any unexpected delays and to give yourself time to settle in.\n\n4. **Identification and Paperwork**: Bring necessary identification and any required paperwork, such as tax forms and identification for employment verification.\n\n5. **Know Your Team**: Be prepared to meet your coworkers and supervisors. Understanding the team structure and knowing who to go to for questions or support is essential.\n\n6. **Theme Park Knowledge**: Familiarize yourself with Universal\u2019s parks, attractions, and experiences. This knowledge can be helpful, especially if you\u2019re working in guest services or a front-line role.\n\n7. **Safety Protocols**: Understand the safety protocols and emergency procedures specific to your workplace, as safety is a top priority in any theme park environment.\n\n8. **Company Culture**: Learn about Universal's culture, values, and mission. Embracing the company's ethos can help you integrate better and feel like part of the team.\n\n9. **Benefits and Resources**: Review information about employee benefits, such as health insurance, employee discounts, and professional development opportunities.\n\n10. **Communication Channels**: Know how to communicate with your team, supervisors, and HR. This may include understanding company email, internal messaging systems, or any other communication tools.\n\n11. **Guest Experience Focus**: Universal emphasizes customer service, so be prepared to engage with guests positively. Understanding the importance of guest experience will be vital in your role.\n\n12. **Ask Questions**: Don\u2019t hesitate to ask questions if you\u2019re unsure about something. It\u2019s a great way to learn and show that you\u2019re eager to understand your new environment.\n\n13. **Stay Positive and Open-Minded**: Starting a new job can come with challenges. Maintain a positive attitude and be open to learning and adapting.\n\nBy keeping these points in mind, new employees can feel more prepared and confident as they embark on their journey at Universal.",
